      <h3>The financial state of Canada Post</h3>
  
      <p>
        Canada Post has, for the last 17 years, been seeing a decline in their
        profits as letter delivery becomes replaced by the
        internet, while faster, cheaper competitors such as UPS and FedEx have
        been growing their shares in the parcel delivery market.
        <br /><br />
        On the other hand, they are in a unique position as a federal Crown corporation
        to deliver services to all communities across Canada. As underpinned in initiatives
        such as their introduction of ‚Äòcommunity hub‚Äô-style post offices, they are
        increasing efforts in serving rural areas as part of their solution outside
        of their existing services in order to establish financial self-sustainability.
      </p>
 
      <div>
        <p class="quote">
