    <div>
      <h3>Properly scoping what a postal worker can or cannot do</h3>
     
      <p>
        With the goal of identifying underlying gaps in a Canada Post-based senior check-in service,
        as a first step 
        my team and I created a website mockup introducing our service, which we 
        named Carriers that Care (CtC), to user-test with our target demographic: adults who have an
        elderly loved one who lives alone. 
        <br><br>
        Initial proposals of Carriers that Care
        were met with a lot of hesitation from user testers. Having conducted
        user interviews with seven individuals with ages ranging from 20s to
        50s, centering our questions around allowed us to sort concerns into
        four categories:
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
